    • Method Detail

      • exec

        U exec(TerminalScanner scan,
       DataModel model,
       User user)
throws PermissionException,
       CancelException,
       java.lang.IllegalArgumentException,
       java.lang.IllegalStateException
        Execute this command and possibly return a result.
        Parameters:
        scan - The scanner used to interact with the person.
        model - The model used for model access.
        user - The User who wants to executes this command.
        Returns:
        null if there is no result specified.
        Throws:
        PermissionException - When the user does not have sufficient permissions.
        CancelException - When the users wants to abort the current cmd
        java.lang.IllegalStateException - When the subject is in an illegal state to perform this cmd.
        java.lang.IllegalArgumentException - When any of the arguments is null and shouldn't be or when in the scenario a chosen option conflicted.
